channel.title: Error Message
channel.description:
Ok im a bit new to SCAR and SRL so heres what my problem is. I DLed SCAR and then DLed SRL v3.6 ok then I extracted the files as instructed so that my SRL files are in my SCAR folder. When I try to rerun the script as instructed to do so after adding it to the included folder in the SCAR directory I get the following message upon hitting run.
[code]Failed when compiling Line 26: [Error] (42:1): Duplicate identifier 'UpChars' in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 3.12\includes\srl\srl\core\Globals.scar[/code]
Can someone please help me and inform me as to what I am doing wrong.

item.title: Error Message
item.dc:creator: @belgin_fish belgin fish
item.description:
@belgin_fish wrote:

it’s not your fault, it’s the script. It looks to me like the author of the script declared UpChars as his own variable or something in the script, and it’s already declared in srl
